OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Mon 20 Jul to Wed 29 Jul
OL,6,FRemaining predominantly dry for most
OL,7,Fparts of the country as high pressure
OL,8,Fis likely to remain close to the UK
OL,9,Ffor much of this period. However, with
OL,10,Fthe source region of the air being
OL,11,Ffrom the North Atlantic, it will be
OL,12,Fless hot compared to many recent days.
OL,13,FAny showers during the start of the
OL,14,Fperiod are more likely across the far
OL,15,Fnorth. Towards the latter part of
OL,16,FJuly, the influence of high pressure
OL,17,Fmay wane somewhat, allowing a greater
OL,18,Fchance of rain, showers or
OL,19,Fthunderstorms compared to earlier in
OL,20,Fthe month, these initially more likely
OL,21,Facross the north before possibly
OL,22,Ftransferring south. Overall,
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Ftemperatures are expected to remain
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,Fabove average during this period.
